 many articles in the press, ranging from [[Gizmodo]],<ref>Nick Stango, \"[https://gizmodo.com/5958549/top-25-nate-silver-facts Top 25 Nate Silver Facts] {{Webarchive|url=https://web.archive.org/web/20170801235117/http://gizmodo.com/5958549/top-25-nate-silver-facts |date=August 1, 2017 }}\", [[Gizmodo]], November 7, 2012.</ref> to online and mainstream newspapers,<ref>Chris Taylor, \"[http://mashable.com/2012/11/07/nate-silver-wins/ The Triumph of the Nerds] {{Webarchive|url=https://web.archive.org/web/20121108050813/http://mashable.com/2012/11/07/nate-silver-wins/ |date=November 8, 2012 }}\", [[Mashable]], November 7, 2012]; Jocelyn Noveck, \"He called it, and now Silver's a pop-culture star\", [http://hosted.ap.org/dynamic/stories/U/US_ELECTION_THE_OTHER_WINNER Associated Press, November 9, 2012]; Martin Robbins, \"Can Nate Silver's example save political journalism?\" ''[[The Guardian]]'', November 13, 2012; Ken Bensinger, \"[http://www.latimes.com/news/nationworld/nation/la-fi-election-math-20121108,0,2926239.story Number crunchers were right about Obama despite what pundits said] {{Webarchive|url=https://web.archive.org/web/20121111064637/http://www.latimes.com/news/nationworld/nation/la-fi-election-math-20121108,0,2926239.story |date=November 11, 2012 }}\", [[Los Angeles Times]], November 8, 2012; James Rainey, \"[http://www.latimes.com/news/politics/la-pn-nate-silver-polls-rasmussen-20121107,0,3329768.story Parsing polls: Nate Silver picks on target, Rasmussen not so much] {{Webarchive|url=https://web.archive.org/web/20121109120837/http://www.latimes.com/news/politics/la-pn-nate-silver-polls-rasmussen-20121107,0,3329768.story |date=November 9, 2012 }}\", ''[[Los Angeles Times]],'' November 8, 2012; Ron Seely, \"[http://host.madison.com/news/science/seely-on-science-nate-silver-gains-fame-by-harnessing-power/article_cf087458-29f8-11e2-a2d4-001a4bcf887a.html?comment_form=true#comments Seely on Science: Nate Silver gains fame by harnessing power of math] {{Webar